channel.description:
[b]Description:[/b] A decent Castle Wars base for a DeltaScape server
[b]Difficulty:[/b] 3.5/10
[b]Tested Server:[/b] DeltaScape
[b]Files/Classes Modified:[/b] client

[i]Note:[/i] This is only a Castle Wars base, you will still need to add the things I left out.

[center][b][u]This base includes but is not limited to:[/u][/b]

[ul][li]Almost all objects are added and handled in the CastleWars class[/li]
[li]All three portals join a team, the Guthix portal will put you on the weaker team[/li]
[li]You cannot attack players on your team[/li]
[li]Scores are recorded and announced at the end of the game[/li]
[li]If you die with the flag, it will be reset[/li]
[li]If you logout with the flag, it will be reset[/li]
[li]All items (except the bronze pick axe) are deleted at the end of the game[/li]
[li]You cannot remove your hood or cape during the game[/li]
[li]You cannot enter a portal while wearing a cape or helmet[/li]
[li]I did not add rewards for winning the game, but feel free to do so on your own[/li]
[li]There are several other things but I wont post them, if you want to know if something is added just ask[/li][/ul]
[/center]

[center][size=14pt][b]Step One:[/b] Adding the CastleWars classes[/size][/center]
[hr]

Download CastleWars.java and CastleWarsHandler.java and add them to your server files.
[url=http://pastebin.com/8UkXtbZq]CastleWars.java[/url]
[url=http://pastebin.com/ESJvU9MF]CastleWarsHandler.java[/url]

Open client class and add
[code=Java]	private CastleWars castlewars = new CastleWars(this);[/code]

Open server class and add
[code=Java]
	public static CastleWarsHandler castleWars = new CastleWarsHandler();[/code]
Also add
[code=Java]
	public static int saradominScore;
	public static int zamorakScore;
	public static boolean saradominStandardTaken;
	public static boolean zamorakStandardTaken;[/code]

Open process class and below
[code=Java]server.playerHandler.process();[/code]
add
[code=Java]server.castleWars.process();[/code]
[i]This will call CastleWarsHandler's process method every half second (500 milliseconds)
The process method in CastleWarsHandler contains the game timer that starts and ends each game.[/i]




[center][size=14pt][b]Step Two:[/b] Adding all the objects[/size][/center]
[hr]

Rather than giving you a large snippet to throw into your client class I put all the objects in CastleWars class, so this is an easy step.

Open client class and find your object clicking packet
[code=Java]case 132:[/code]
Locate
[code=Java]if (objectID == [/code]
Above that add
[code=Java]for (int obs : castlewars.objects)
	if (objectID == obs)
		castlewars.handleCastleWarsObjects(objectID, objectX, objectY);[/code]
[i]This checks to see if the clicked object is a Castle Wars object.[/i]



[center][size=14pt][b]Step Three:[/b] Showing the game interface and waiting interface[/size][/center]
[hr]

In client class find
[code=Java]public boolean process() {[/code]
Add below
[code=Java]
	if (castlewars.isInCastleWars())
		castlewars.displayGameFrame();
	if (castlewars.isInSaradomin() || castlewars.isInZamorak())
		castlewars.displayRemainingTime();[/code]
[i]This checks to see if you are in a game or waiting to enter a game, than displays the appropriate interface[/i]




[center][size=14pt][b]Step Four:[/b] Keeping capes and hoods and things on for the duration of the game.[/size][/center]
[hr]

In client class find
[code=Java]public void remove(int wearID, int slot)[/code]
Add below
[code=Java]
	if ((castlewars.isInCastleWars() || castlewars.isInSaradomin() || castlewars.isInZamorak()) && (wearID == 4037 || wearID == 4039 || wearID == 4513 || wearID == 4514 || wearID == 4515 || wearID == 4516)) {
		sM("You may not remove this.");
		return;
	}[/code]
[i]Prevents you from taking off the specified items.[/i]

Find
[code=Java]public boolean wear(int wearID, int slot)[/code]
Add below
[code=Java]
	if ((castlewars.isInCastleWars() || castlewars.isInSaradomin() || castlewars.isInZamorak()) && itemType(wearID) == 1) {
		sM("You may not put on a cape here.");
		return false;
	}
	if ((castlewars.isInCastleWars() || castlewars.isInSaradomin() || castlewars.isInZamorak()) && itemType(wearID) == 0) {
		sM("You may not put on a hat or helmet here.");
		return false;
	}
	if (castlewars.isInCastleWars() && (playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 4037 || playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 4037)) {
		sM("You can't take off the flag, make a run for it ;)");
		return false;
	}[/code]
[i]The first if-statement prevents capes from being put on.
The second if-statement prevents hats and helmets from being put on.
The third and final if-statement prevents you from putting on weapons when you have the flag. Why? Because I felt like it ;) [/i]




[center][size=14pt][b]Step Five:[/b] Creating the safe pvp multi-combat zone[/size][/center]
[hr]

In client class find
[code=Java]public boolean isInWilderness(int coordX, int coordY, int Type) {[/code]
Under
[code=Java]if (Type == 1) {[/code]
Add
[code=Java]
	if (castlewars.isInCastleWars())
		return true;[/code]
[i]This will make the Castle Wars area a PvP area.[/i]

Find
[code=Java]if ((AttackingOn2.combatLevel + wildyLevel < combatLevel || combatLevel + wildyLevel < AttackingOn2.combatLevel) && !isInPitGame()) {[/code]
Replace with
[code=Java]if ((AttackingOn2.combatLevel + wildyLevel < combatLevel || combatLevel + wildyLevel < AttackingOn2.combatLevel) && !isInPitGame() && !castlewars.isInCastleWars()) {[/code]
[i]This will allow you to attack all players, regardless of combat level.[/i]

Find
[code=Java]public boolean multiCombat() {[/code]
Add Under
[code=Java]
	if (castlewars.isInCastleWars())
		return true;[/code]
[i]This makes Castle Wars a multi-combat zone.[/i]

Find
[code=Java]private boolean Attack() {[/code]
Under
[code=Java]	client AttackingOn2 = (client) server.playerHandler.players[AttackingOn];[/code]
Add
[code=Java]
	if (castlewars.isZamorak && AttackingOn2.castlewars.isZamorak) {
		sM("You cannot attack your teammate.");
		ResetAttack();
		return false;
	}
	if (castlewars.isSaradomin && AttackingOn2.castlewars.isSaradomin) {
		sM("You cannot attack your teammate.");
		ResetAttack();
		return false;
	}[/code]



[center][size=14pt][b]Step Six:[/b] Creating appropriate death instances[/size][/center]
[hr]

In client class find
[code=Java]if (!IsInFightCave() && !isInPitGame() && !isInPitRoom()[/code] 
[i]Note this is a partial snippet, the code you will find will be longer than this.[/i]
Add
[code=Java] && !castlewars.isInCastleWars()[/code]
So that it looks something like
[code=Java]if (!IsInFightCave() && !isInPitGame() && !isInPitRoom() && !castlewars.isInCastleWars()[/code]
[i]This ensures that when you die in Castle Wars, you wont lose all your items and get teleported to the normal death zone.[/i]

In the [b]same spot[/b], above that condition (Above the if-statement)
Add
[code=Java]
	if (castlewars.isInCastleWars() && deathStage == 2 && System.currentTimeMillis() - deathTimer >= 2500) {
		client killerz = (client) server.playerHandler.players[KillerId];
		killerz.sM("You have defeated " + playerName + ".");
		toX = castlewars.isZamorak ? 2372 : 2427;
		toY = castlewars.isZamorak ? 3131 : 3076;
		heightLevel = 1;
		if (playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 4037) {
			server.saradominStandardTaken = false;
			playerEquipment[playerWeapon] = -1;
			playerEquipmentN[playerWeapon] = 0;
			setEquipment(-1, 0, playerWeapon);
		}
		if (playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 4039) {
			server.zamorakStandardTaken = false;
			playerEquipment[playerWeapon] = -1;
			playerEquipmentN[playerWeapon] = 0;
			setEquipment(-1, 0, playerWeapon);
		}
		AtkPray = 0;
		StrPrayer = 0;
		DefPray = 0;
		RangePray = 0;
		MagePray = 0;
		PrayHeal = false;
		ProtItem = false;
		ProtMage = false;
		ProtRange = false;
		ProtMelee = false;
		Redemption = false;
		Retribution = false;
		Smite = false;
		Chivalry = false;
		Piety = false;
		isSkulled = false;
		lastSkull = 0;
		headIcon = 0;
		turnpray();
		currentHealth = playerLevel[playerHitpoints];
		deathStage = 0;
		resetAnimation();
		frame1();
		prayOn = false;
		AntiTeleDelay = 0;
		EntangleDelay = 0;
		sM("Oh dear you have died!");
		resetOtherAtk();
		followID = 0;
		followID2 = 0;
	}[/code]




[center][size=14pt][b]Step Seven:[/b] Removing you from the game if you re-log [/size][/center]
[hr]

In client class find
[code=Java]public void initialize() {[/code]
Under
[code=Java]l33thax(7499);[/code]
Add
[code=Java]
	if (castlewars.isInCastleWars())
		castlewars.removeFromGame();
	if (castlewars.isInZamorak() || castlewars.isInSaradomin()) {
		sM("You have been removed from the waiting room.");
		toX = 2441;
		toY = 3090;
		heightLevel = 0;
		playerEquipment[playerCape] = -1;
		playerEquipment[playerHat] = -1;
		playerEquipmentN[playerCape] = 0;
		playerEquipmentN[playerHat] = 0;
		setEquipment(-1, 0, playerCape);
		setEquipment(-1, 0, playerHat);
	}[/code]




[center][size=14pt][b]Step Eight:[/b] Miscellaneous snippets[/size][/center]
[hr]

[i]These snippets may already be added to your server, check before adding them[/i]

[u]Bandages[/u]
In potions class in the buryItem method add
[code=Java]
	case 4049:
		if (System.currentTimeMillis() - c.foodDelay < 2000)
			return;
		c.foodDelay = System.currentTimeMillis();
		c.currentHealth += 10;
		if (c.currentHealth > c.playerLevel[c.playerHitpoints])
			c.currentHealth = c.playerLevel[c.playerHitpoints];
		c.sendQuest("" + c.currentHealth + "", 4016);
		c.deleteItem(4049, slot, 1);
		break;[/code]

[u]Exploding Potions[/u]
In client class in the dropItem method add
[code=Java]
	if (droppedItem == 4045) {
		deleteItem(4045, 1);
		dealDamage(15);
		hitDiff = 15;
		plrText = "Ouch!";
		plrTextUpdateRequired = true;
		updateRequired = true;
		hitUpdateRequired = true;
		setAnimation(827);
		return;
	}[/code]

[u]Prevent Random Disconnecting[/u]
[i]This is one of the dumbest methods I've seen in a Delta base, if you click too fast, you get kicked...[/i]

In client class find
[code=Java]
public boolean antiHax() {[/code]
Comment out
[code=Java]disconnected = true;[/code]
[i]To comment out a line simply add // in front of it.[/i]

[code=Java]//disconnected = true;[/code]


And there you have it, a decent Castle Wars base.
